# Financial Risk Operational Operating Income from Continuing Operations Before Tax Adjusted Amount

## identifier
de8162

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of adjusted operating income from continuing operations during the relevant period, as determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards.
     
This item represents the following:
     - Total operating income from continuing operations, as determined in accordance with relevant accounting standards; less
     - Adjustments relating to the retail banking and commercial banking areas of business, as determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards; less
     - Any other relevant adjustments, as determined in accordance with relevant prudential standards.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=FinancialRisk.Operational.OperatingIncomefromContinuingOperationsBeforeTaxAdjusted.Amount
- classification=baf/bafot/bafot.02.06
- period=duration
